In its time this Bodleian book has been the property of two Yorkshiremen, men of renown: Ralph Thoresby and Marmaduke Fothergill. Thoresby describes it in the cata- logue of his Museum as ‘ perfect, and a great curiosity: and gives the summary of its contentS.² After Thoresby's death · in 1725 it passed into the hands os Marmaduke Fothergill.
